EmailTemplate.subject: SunPower SolarNow Program with Enerbank: {!Account.Name}
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
{!TODAY()}
RE: SunPower SolarNow Program with Enerbank
Dear {!Contact.FirstName},
Thank you for choosing SunPower SolarNow Program!
Our partner for this program is a member of FDIC ENERBANK USA
Dealer should be an active member of the program before offering this option to their potential customers. Here are the steps:
1. SunPower will be sending the SAC dealer agreement via echosign; please provide the contact information of the person (Name and email) who will be signing the agreement.
2. Dealers must watch the training available at SunPower University:
a) Log on to the dealer portal
b) Launch SunPower University located at the left portion of the page
c) In the search box, type in the title of the course: SolarNow Loan Program-Enerbank Partner Portal Training; click Add to Learning Plan
d) On your learning plan, search for the course title and click Go to Content
e) Once you have successfully finished the course, you can view them on the Learning History button.
3. Dealers must read the General Training Deck: SolarNow Payment Option and other SolarNow-related documents available in the Content tab of the partner portal. Locate the file by typing in the search box the title SolarNow.
4. Dealers must fill out the FPAF (see attached) and submit with the scanned copy of the voided check (copy must be clear and readable) to financing@sunpower.com. If voided check is not available, send the scanned copy of the bank letter.
IMPORTANT:
Make sure that the FPAF is filled out correctly. The address on the check/bank letter and on the FPAF must be exactly the same. Otherwise, the form will be returned to dealer for correction. Being in a much regulated industry, ENERBANK requires all forms to be filled out perfectly.
5. Dealers must fill out the Contact Information Page form (see attached), and submit to financing@sunpower.com.
6. Once the documents are submitted, these will be sent to Enerbank to finalize the enrollment process.
7. Enerbank will be contacting the dealer to set expectations, discuss best practices, and schedule the training.
8. Enerbank will train the dealer's sales team and officially activate them as SunPower Solar SAC dealer.
Should you have questions, please contact us at 1-800-SUNPOWER or send an email to financing@sunpower.com.
Respectfully,
Customer Financing Team
